Easing - Interface in tracer.easings
Represents an easing curve (AKA a tweening curve) that controls the speed of an animation over time.
easing() - Method in class tracer.paths.Gesture
Flattens the Gesture, which has 3 dimensions (2 spatial dimensions and 1 temporal dimension), to create an Easing, which has 2 dimensions (1 spatial dimension and 1 temporal dimension), and returns the Easing.
